txt.en: Cousin o' mine wandered into the Old Forest when we was little. He came out white as a sheet.
The constable's been busy as a bees in a hive, what with all the strangers coming an going.
Oh, it's gonna get fierce cold this winter, ye mark my words.
Mind ye don't stray too far west o' the Greenway. Them hills are a lonely place an' they leech the hope right out o' ye.
Early to bed, early to rise, that's what my old dad used to say...never figured out what he meant by it.
Never seem to have enough time.
Are ye one o' them raggedy folk from the south or, worse yet, one o' them Rangers?
If ye ask me, those Little Folk ought to get out in the sun more. Really, what's the thinking behind living in holes?.
Sometimes the sunset over the Downs makes me wish I owned a horse.
